{
  "text": "Hydroxyl radical yields were measured by comparing the EPR spectral intensity of pure ice with the spectral intensity of an oligodeoxynucleotide crystal irradiated with the same dose, 22 kGy. The downfield features of the hydroxyl radical spectrum, which are well outside any features found from the spectra of DNA radicals, are shown in Fig. 2 . Of these features, one was used as the reference feature for comparing the two spectra [CITATION_1] . Alignment of the spectra was made using the spectral lines of H",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "27316007"
